value:
Into your hands, I commend
	my spirit, my soul, my body;
you created them, redeemed them, gave them new birth,
	O Lord, the God of truth.
And you have given me all that is with me, and all that is mine,
	O Lord, in your goodness.
Watch over my lying down and my waking up,
	from this time forth for evermore;
to remember you upon my bed,
	to search out my spirit;
to wake up and still remain with you.
I lie down in peace; at once I fall asleep;
	for only you, Lord, make me dwell in safety.

value.text:
Forgiveness and release
	from all my sins
	and all my offenses;

That we may pass the rest of our lives
	in repentance and awe,
	in health and peace;

Whatever is true, whatever is noble,
whatever is right, whatever is holy,
whatever is pleasant, whatever is good,
if there be any virtue and there be any praise,
that we may think these things, and do them;
